The paper focuses on training state-of-the-art visual understanding neural networks on the ImageNet-1K dataset using Integer operations on General Purpose (GP) hardware. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the nuances of developing an efficient integer convolution kernel, which falls under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also proposes a shared exponent representation of tensors and develops a Dynamic Fixed Point (DFP) scheme suitable for common neural network operations, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with mixed precision training, which could fall under the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
